    <item>
      <title>Categories and Tags in Blogs</title>
      <link>/post/categories-and-tags-in-blogs/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 22 May 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>/post/categories-and-tags-in-blogs/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Last Updated: 2025-11-04&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;tldr&#34;&gt;TL;DR&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Categories&lt;/strong&gt; are broad topics that help you organize your blog posts, and help readers find the information they’re seeking on your site.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tags&lt;/strong&gt; are a simple way to drill down on the topic of any given blog post that’s part of a category.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;description&#34;&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;These two words may be used interchangeably, but they are not the same thing. The difference is simple: A category is a broad topic you cover in your blog. It acts as the umbrella to a bunch of smaller topics. Blog tags are one small idea in an overarching topic.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
